body_html: @aselle @wolffg Just wonder how does https://www.tensorflow.org resolve the url, seems that it can resolve https://www.tensorflow.org/code/tensorflow/contrib/deprecated/summaries_test.py to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/deprecated/summaries_test.py successfully while failed for __init__.py. One possible reason is that the "_" is some kind of special character for the URL resolver. It's better for us to check this first, otherwise we can just simply change https://www.tensorflow.org/code/tensorflow/contrib/deprecated/__init__.py to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/deprecated/__init__.py
